The paper deals with the problem of finding and counting certain types of repeats in strings, which is a classic problem in computer science. The techniques used in the paper involve data structures, combinatorics, and information theory, which are all relevant to the aforementioned sub-categories. Additionally, the authors cite several papers from these sub-categories in their related work section.
